    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix emm_main_is_attached() logic for emergency attachment handling\n\n### Summary\nThe `emm_main_is_attached()` function was incorrectly returning true for emergency-only attachments, causing conflicts with normal EPS service procedures. This fix ensures the function only returns true for normal EPS attachments, not emergency-only ones.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/emm_main.c`: Modified `emm_main_is_attached()` to check `emm_data->is_attached && !emm_data->is_emergency`\n- `openair3/NAS/UE/EMM/emm_main.c`: Updated function documentation to reflect the change in behavior\n\n### Reproduction\nBefore this fix, when a UE was attached for emergency services only:\n1. `emm_main_is_attached()` would return true\n2. This would cause the NAS procedure to incorrectly attempt normal EPS procedures\n3. The separate emergency handling logic would never be reached\n\nAfter this fix:\n1. Emergency-only attachment correctly returns false from `emm_main_is_attached()`\n2. Normal EPS attachment correctly returns true from `emm_main_is_attached()`\n3. Emergency handling can proceed through the dedicated `emm_main_is_emergency()` path\n"
}